<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-70-0095 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book provides an overview of the effects of several abused drugs,including opiates, cannabinoids, alcohol, nicotine, and cocaine, withspecial emphasis on the actions of these substances at the molecularand cellular levels. The first half deals with genetic effects, includingmolecular genetics, biochemical genetics, pharmacogenetics, cytogenetics,and genetic toxicity. The second half focuses on perinatal effects andcovers: drug abuse during pregnancy; biochemical aspects of marihuanaon male reproduction; and long-term behavioral and neuroendocrine effectsof perinatal alcohol exposure.</TEXT></DOC>